  E-Sliding Join Window
  F-Sliding Aggregation Window.



Suppressed :

By default, aggregated window results are emitted based on commit.interval.ms (e.g., every 30s)

L'opérateur de suppression(suppressed) dans Kafka Streams est un outil puissant permettant de contrôler
le moment où les résultats d'agrégation par fenêtre sont émis en aval (downstream).
 Il vous aide à éviter d'émettre des résultats intermédiaires
 et à attendre plutôt des résultats plus complets ou finaux.

 The Problem It Solves
 Without suppress, windowed aggregations emit results every time a new record updates the window. This means:

 You get many intermediate updates for the same window
 Downstream systems receive incomplete data repeatedly
 It creates unnecessary processing overhead
 Results are emitted even while the window is still open and receiving data

 To achieve that we need 3 differentes configuration:


  1-Suppression Config
     have 2 differentes config :
       1-1 Suppressed.unitlWindowCloses  ==> only emit the result after the defined window is closed
       1-2 Suppressed.unitlTimeLimit     ==> only emit the result if there are no successive events for the defined time.
        Let's say if you pass the value as five seconds to it. In that case,
        if there are no events received with that five second interval, then in that case, it will emit the results downstream.
  2-Buffer Config
     BufferConfig.MaxByte(): total number of bytes the buffer can hold
     BufferConfig.MaxRecords():total number of records the buffer can hold
     BufferConfig.unBounded():Represents unbounded memory to hold the records

  3-Buffer full Config
     shutDownWhenFUll : shutdown the app if the buffer is full
     emitEarlyWhenFull : emit the intermediate results if the buffer is full
